81.6	Potentiometer	Potentiometer	A potentiometer ( ), informally, a pot, in electronics technology is a component, a three-terminal resistor with a sliding contact that forms an adjustable voltage divider. If only two terminals are used, one end and the wiper, it acts as a variable resistor or rheostat.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Potentiometer.jpg/225px-Potentiometer.jpg
